<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="E" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Expedition" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Expedition,</orth> 1) haste, dispatch: <bibl n="shak. tgv 1.3.37" default="NO" valid="yes">Gentl. I, 3, 37</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 3.1.164" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 164</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 1.2.458" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. I, 2, 458</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 4.3.37" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B IV, 3, 37</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 4.3.54" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 IV, 3, 54</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 5.2.3" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. V, 2, 3</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 2.3.116" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. II, 3, 116</bibl>. Used as the name of a ship: <bibl n="shak. err 4.3.38" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. IV, 3, 38</bibl>.<lb />2) march of an army: <cit><quote>before your e. to Shrewsbury,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 1.2.116" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B I, 2, 116</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>let us deliver our puissance into the hand of God, putting it straight in e.</quote> <bibl n="shak. h5 2.2.191" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 II, 2, 191</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>who intercepts my e.?</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 4.4.136" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 IV, 4, 136</bibl></cit> (Ff <emph>me in my e.</emph>). <cit><quote>bending their e. toward Philippi,</quote> <bibl n="shak. jc 4.3.170" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. IV, 3, 170</bibl></cit>.
<lb />3) warlike enterprise: <bibl n="shak. jn 1.49" default="NO" valid="yes">John I, 49</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 2.79.170" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 79</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 1.3.150" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A I, 3, 150</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 4.3.19" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 19</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 1.2.249" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B I, 2, 249</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 1.2.301" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 I, 2, 301</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 4.4.2" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A IV, 4, 2</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 4.4.2" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A IV, 4, 2</bibl> <bibl n="shak. cor 2.1.169" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. II, 1, 169</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 1.3.229" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. I, 3, 229</bibl>.
<lb />4) any enterprise implying a change of place: <bibl n="shak. tgv 1.3.77" default="NO" valid="yes">Gentl. I, 3, 77</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 5.1.6" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 6</bibl>.
<lb />Misapplied by Fluellen: <bibl n="shak. h5 3.2.82" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 III, 2, 82</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>